<i>adverb</i>: 확실히 [확씰히], 하릴없이 [하ː리럽씨], 필연코 [피련코], 필연 [피련], 필시 [필씨], 어련히 [어련히], 반드시 [반드시], 똑 [똑], 두말없이 [두ː마럽씨], 꼭 [꼭], 그야말로 [그야말로] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt>확실히 [확씰히]</dt><br>
<dd>certainly; surely; confidently; definitely</dd><br>
<dd>실제와 꼭 같거나 틀림없이 그러하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of being absolutely true or being certain of something.</dd><br>
<dt>하릴없이 [하ː리럽씨]</dt><br>
<dd>1. helplessly</dd><br>
<dd>달리 어떻게 할 방법이 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of having no choice but to do something.</dd><br>
<dd>2. certainly; surely; exactly</dd><br>
<dd>조금도 틀림이 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Absolutely correct.</dd><br>
<dt>필연코 [피련코]</dt><br>
<dd>certainly; surely; without fail</dd><br>
<dd>(강조하는 말로) 조금도 어긋나지 않고 반드시.</dd><br>
<dd>(emphatic form) Certainly, without fail.</dd><br>
<dt>필연 [피련]</dt><br>
<dd>certainly; surely; without fail</dd><br>
<dd>조금도 어긋나지 않고 반드시.</dd><br>
<dd>Certainly, without fail.</dd><br>
<dt>필시 [필씨]</dt><br>
<dd>certainly; surely</dd><br>
<dd>거의 어긋나는 일이 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Almost without any doubt.</dd><br>
<dt>어련히 [어련히]</dt><br>
<dd>definitely; certainly; absolutely</dd><br>
<dd>걱정하지 않아도 될 만큼 잘될 것이 분명하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a definite manner in which there is no need to worry because things will turn out fine.</dd><br>
<dt>반드시 [반드시]</dt><br>
<dd>without fail; certainly</dd><br>
<dd>틀림없이 꼭.</dd><br>
<dd>Surely.</dd><br>
<dt>똑 [똑]</dt><br>
<dd>certainly; surely; exactly</dd><br>
<dd>조금도 틀림이 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Exactly right in every way.</dd><br>
<dt>두말없이 [두ː마럽씨]</dt><br>
<dd>1. without complaint</dd><br>
<dd>이런저런 불평을 하거나 덧붙이는 말이 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Without any complaint or additional comment.</dd><br>
<dd>2. definitely; certainly</dd><br>
<dd>더 말할 필요도 없이 확실하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Definitely without having to say anything further.</dd><br>
<dt>꼭 [꼭]</dt><br>
<dd>1. without fail; at any cost; certainly</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일이 있어도 반드시.</dd><br>
<dd>By all means under any circumstances.</dd><br>
<dd>2. precisely</dd><br>
<dd>조금도 다르지 않고 정확하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Exactly without any difference.</dd><br>
<dd>3. perfectly</dd><br>
<dd>아주 잘.</dd><br>
<dd>Very well.</dd><br>
<dd>4. satisfactorily</dd><br>
<dd>매우 만족스럽게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a very satisfactory manner.</dd><br>
<dd>5. as if; just like</dd><br>
<dd>매우 비슷하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a very similar way.</dd><br>
<dt>그야말로 [그야말로]</dt><br>
<dd>certainly; indeed; really</dd><br>
<dd>(강조하는 말로) 사실 그대로.</dd><br>
<dd>(emphasizing form) Truly.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>